{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489703","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489703"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:26:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:26:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"722"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"722","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/722"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.13,0.78,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"722"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47026"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"722","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/722"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"722"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"31783"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"97"},{"type":"tags","id":"1126"},{"type":"tags","id":"2165"},{"type":"tags","id":"4789"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12913"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1892"},{"type":"contributions","id":"12397"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42133"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44471"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47026","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/47026"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 47-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a three-day history of severe anorectal pain associated with the passage of small amounts of bright red blood. The blood is present at the end of defaecation and visible on the toilet paper. He notices that defaecation is extremely uncomfortable and he is left with a stinging sensation in his perineal region which lasts for about 30 minutes. These symptoms started after a bout of severe constipation that lasted for five days. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely explanation for his symptoms?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Thrombosed internal haemorrhoid","Thrombosed external haemorrhoid","Acute anal fissure","Pruritis ani","Anal squamous cell carcinoma"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhilst any of the conditions listed could present with the passage of bright red blood per rectum, the description of acute pain on defaecation and lingering discomfort fits best for an \u003Cstrong\u003Eacute anal fissure\u003C/strong\u003E. Such acute fissures may develop after anal trauma associated with the passage of a constipated and hard stool.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThrombosed internal or external haemorrhoids\u003C/strong\u003E would also have pain as part of their symptomatology, however the pain would be persistent and not settle so soon after defaecation as typically occurs with an anal fissure. In addition, there tends to be larger volumes of bleeding with internal haemorrhoids and associated mucus discharge. In reality, there is often considerable variation in the symptoms associated with an anal fissure and internal haemorrhoids and a careful physical examination will be require to distinguish between the two problems.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPruritis ani\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by itching around the anus. While it can be associated with bleeding if the skin becomes excoriated from scratching, it would not typically cause the severe pain on defecation described in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnal squamous cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E can present with bleeding and pain. However, the acute onset after constipation and the characteristic pain that settles after defecation makes anal fissure much more likely in this case. Anal cancer would be more likely to have persistent symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Sharp pain and bleeding on defaecation is usually due to an anal fissure."],"references":["Lu Y, Kwaan MR, Lin AY. Diagnosis and Treatment of Anal Fissures in 2021. JAMA 2021;325:688-89. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33591336/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"31783"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"722"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"31783","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/31783"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-06-14T21:34:51+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-08-01T20:40:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"722"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47026"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{